OL,3,COwners of airport promise to improve
OL,4,Caccess following fatal hit and run
OL,6,FA spokesperson from Bournemouth
OL,7,FAirport said: "Following the accident,
OL,8,Fwe renewed our efforts to work with
OL,9,Fthe local authority and local bus
OL,10,Fcompany to improve public transport
OL,11,Faccess and promote pedestrian safety.
OL,13,F"In the intervening period, we have
OL,14,Fmade substantive progress including
OL,15,Four plans to increase the frequency of
OL,16,Fbus services and create a dedicated
OL,17,Fpedestrian footpath alongside Hurn
OL,18,FCourt Lane, and our success in
OL,19,Fsecuring a commitment from the local
OL,20,Fauthority to reduce the speed limit on
OL,21,FParley Lane from 60mph to 40mph."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/6
